This paper is primarily focused on face recognition and image synthesis, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also proposes a novel approach to representation learning using a generative adversarial network, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on several databases, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or graphics (cs.GR) categories.
